| project
    User = User,
    FileAccessCount = FileAccessCount,
    CloudUploadCount = CloudUploadCount,
    Pattern = "File access followed by cloud upload",
    Severity = "Critical"
*/

// TUNING PARAMETERS:
// FileAccessCount >= 5: Adjust based on normal user download patterns
// FilesPerMinute >= 2: Rapid download detection threshold
// EventID values: 5145 (share access), 5140 (share object access)
// File types: Add other sensitive extensions specific to your environment
// Share names: Add other sensitive locations (accounting, engineering, etc.)

// NOTES:
// - Exfiltration often precedes cloud uploads (copy files locally first)
// - Bulk downloads of sensitive files = strong exfiltration indicator
// - Archives (.zip, .rar) are favorite exfiltration containers
// - Database files (.mdb, .db, .sql) indicate sensitive data theft
// - Rapid downloads (2+ files/min) = automated tool or urgent exfil
// - Review SourceIP - external IPs more suspicious than internal
// - User accounts shouldn't access finance/HR/legal shares normally
// - Correlate with network data transfer volume for more context
// - Large file transfers may also indicate exfiltration
// - Requires Windows Event Forwarding or Sysmon for reliable detection
// - Can combine with DLP (Data Loss Prevention) alerts for additional confirmation
